<task id="019" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-10 Slash command `/summarize` semantic extension (tri-mode intent routing)</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>1.5 hours (sub-agent code-authoring; quality gates + tests + smoke deferred to main session per executor instructions)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G5 (parallel-safe; no deps; siblings 020, 021, 022)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none (UI-only; consumes ChatSession.UploadedFiles surfaced by task 004 + InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool from task 015 OR endpoint from task 014 at runtime)</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, slash-command, intent-router</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the EXISTING `/summarize` slash command in `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` (in
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SlashCommandMenu/slashCommandMenu.types.ts`)
    so that it semantically supports both modes that R5 now ships: session-uploaded
    files AND the active analysis document (back-compat wizard flow). The change is
    two-fold:

    (1) Update the `/summarize` entry's `description` text to "Summarize uploaded
        files or the active document" — the menu subtitle is the user's primary
        signal that both modes exist, so the wording MUST signal both clearly.

    (2) Wire the SpaarkeAi shell's intent-handler (the `onSend` handoff in
        `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx` —
        the file that consumes `SprkChat` from `@spaarke/ui-components` and is the
        single dispatch site for `/summarize`-prefixed messages) to apply tri-mode
        routing per FR-03 of `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md`:

          a) IF the active `ChatSession.UploadedFiles.length > 0` (manifest extension
             from task 004) → route to the session-files Summarize path. The agent-
             tool path is preferred (LLM calls `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` from task
             015); fallback / explicit-slash dispatch is the direct endpoint from
             task 014 (`POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize`). Both
             converge on the shared `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012) so the
             routing decision in this file is just a path selector — no orchestration
             logic.

          b) ELSE IF an active workspace document is present (existing
             `WorkspaceTabManager` selection or `documentId` propagated through
             `SprkChat` props per the R3/R4 wizard contract) → fall through to the
             EXISTING Summarize wizard flow (`SummarizeFilesDialog` / `streamSummarize`
             pattern shipped in R3, used by LegalWorkspace + SummarizeFilesWizard
             today). This MUST remain functional unchanged — the wizard is a
             back-compat consumer + the wider Summarize entry point for non-chat
             surfaces.

          c) ELSE (neither uploaded files nor active document — the FR-03 prompt-
             first path) → emit a deterministic chat-layer interjection "Upload the
             file(s) you'd like me to summarize" in the ConversationPane. The
             interjection is rendered as an Assistant message (per the existing
             `addMessage` pattern that `SprkChat`'s `handleSend` already uses for
             user messages); the playbook is NOT invoked.

    R5 is configuration-first and reuse-first: this task adds ZERO BFF code, ZERO
    new slash-command frameworks, ZERO new event channels (ADR-030 closed at 4),
    and ZERO new feature flags (ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline). It EXTENDS the
    existing `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` constant — does NOT introduce a parallel
    slash-command system. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB by construction (frontend
    only).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React 19 + TypeScript developer with deep familiarity with the SpaarkeAi
    three-pane shell, the `@spaarke/ui-components` SprkChat surface, the existing
    `useSlashCommands` / `SlashCommandMenu` machinery, and the LegalWorkspace
    SummarizeFilesDialog back-compat wizard path. Comfortable with intent-routing
    UI logic, Fluent UI v9 conventions (ADR-021), and ChatSession.UploadedFiles
    semantics from task 004.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `/summarize` shows "Summarize uploaded files or the active document" in the
    SlashCommandMenu subtitle on Spaarke Dev. The ConversationPane intent-handler
    applies tri-mode routing per FR-03: uploaded-files-present → session-files
    Summarize path (agent-tool or direct endpoint); no uploaded files but active
    workspace document → existing wizard flow (back-compat verified working);
    neither → deterministic "Upload the file(s) you'd like me to summarize"
    interjection in the chat thread. Existing wizard consumers
    (`SummarizeFilesWizard` solution; `LegalWorkspace`'s `SummarizeFilesDialog`)
    behave unchanged. Frontend tests cover all three branches plus the back-compat
    case. `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5. BFF
    publish-size delta = 0 MB (confirmed in task notes; no BFF code changed).
  </goal>

