  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-03">Two valid file upload orderings — both must reach the same Summarize playbook invocation. The prompt-first path interjects "Upload the file(s) you'd like me to summarize" via chat-layer logic (NOT playbook-emitted). This task implements the chat-layer interjection branch.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-01">`/summarize` resolves to the Summarize playbook (GUID `4a72f99c-a119-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988` for the existing wizard playbook; session-files Summarize uses the new `sprk_analysisaction` seed from task 010 — both share the playbook entrypoint contract).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-12">Tool description quality — slash command description text is part of the user-facing scope signal that prevents misrouting between `summarize` and `insights.query`. "Summarize uploaded files or the active document" deliberately keeps the scope file-centric (not entity-centric, which is the `insights.query` lane).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">MUST extend the EXISTING `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` entry. MUST NOT introduce a parallel slash-command system, a new menu component, or a new dispatch framework. Routing logic lives in the existing ConversationPane `onSend` handler.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4 + ADR-030">PaneEventBus channels are closed at 4. This task MUST NOT add a new channel. If the interjection uses PaneEventBus at all, it MUST be an additive event type within an existing channel (likely none — interjection is local chat-state addMessage, no cross-pane dispatch needed).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 + ADR-018">R5 introduces ZERO new feature flags. Tri-mode routing is unconditional behavior, not flag-gated.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">SlashCommandMenu type definitions live in `@spaarke/ui-components` and MUST remain context-agnostic — no `Xrm` or `ComponentFramework` imports. The intent-handler in ConversationPane is allowed to consume the host context (`SpaarkeAi` shell context, `AiSessionProvider`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Any UI text (description, interjection message) MUST work in dark mode and use Fluent v9 semantic tokens if any visual styling is introduced. The interjection rendering reuses existing assistant-message styling — no new styling expected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 throughout — new logic in ConversationPane uses existing React 19 hooks and the existing SprkChat `addMessage` / `handleSend` patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (frontend-only change). MUST confirm in task notes; no `dotnet publish` measurement required for this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Back-compat MUST be preserved: existing `SummarizeFilesDialog` consumers (LegalWorkspace, SummarizeFilesWizard solution) MUST continue to function unchanged. The wizard flow is the "no uploaded files but active workspace document" branch; verify by smoke test against an existing LegalWorkspace surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">The `description` text MUST be exactly "Summarize uploaded files or the active document" per plan.md D2-10 + spec FR-03 acceptance criteria. Wording is deliberate (file-centric, dual-mode, not too long for the menu subtitle column).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Interjection text MUST be "Upload the file(s) you'd like me to summarize" (sentence case; mirrors the playful-but-precise tone of existing SprkChat assistant interjections). Rendered as a single Assistant message; no avatar variation; no PaneEventBus broadcast.</constraint>
  </constraints>

