      (014 + 015 + 016) are progressing so the tri-mode dispatch targets exist;
      if 014/015 are still in flight, document the runtime-coordination note in
      task notes (this task is UI-only and can ship its routing logic ahead of
      the endpoint/tool landing, but smoke testing requires both).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically
      confirm: (a) the current `description` value in `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS`
      for the `summarize` entry; (b) the host dispatch site in `ConversationPane`
      that consumes SprkChat's `onSend`; (c) the `useSlashCommands` hook contract
      (does the menu close + write the trigger to the textarea, then user sends?
      yes — confirm); (d) the existing `SummarizeFilesDialog` invocation surface
      so the back-compat branch dispatches correctly.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Plan Implementation">
      Confirm three discrete edits + their test counterparts:
      (1) `slashCommandMenu.types.ts` — change one string literal in the
          `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` `summarize` entry's `description`.
      (2) `ConversationPane.tsx` — add tri-mode intent-routing logic in the
          message dispatch path. Surface the routing as a small, named helper
          function (e.g., `routeSummarizeIntent(messageText, session, hostContext)`)
          to keep dispatch logic testable.
      (3) Tests — add or update component tests covering all four cases:
          (a) uploaded-files-present → session-files path dispatched;
          (b) no uploaded files + active document → wizard dispatched;
          (c) neither → interjection rendered;
          (d) back-compat — existing wizard consumers (LegalWorkspace) work
          unchanged when invoked outside ConversationPane.
      Decide on the routing-helper signature + interjection-rendering mechanism
      (programmatic `addMessage` via SprkChat callback vs `predefinedPrompts`
      injection vs new optional callback prop on SprkChat); document the
      decision in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Update Slash Command Description">
      Edit `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SlashCommandMenu/slashCommandMenu.types.ts`:
      change the `description` field on the `summarize` entry of
      `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` from `'Summarize the current analysis document'`
      to `'Summarize uploaded files or the active document'`. Preserve every
      other field on that entry verbatim (id, label, trigger, icon, category,
      source).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Tri-Mode Intent Handler">
      In `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx`,
      add tri-mode routing for `/summarize`-prefixed messages (or for any
      message routed via a slash-command path the host can identify). The
      routing helper inspects:
        - `chatSession.uploadedFiles?.length ?? 0` (or the bridge analog if
          task 004 has not yet landed; document the choice)
        - active workspace document context (existing `documentId` /
          `WorkspaceTabManager` state)
      and dispatches as follows:
        - branch (a) uploaded-files: dispatch the session-files Summarize via
          the agent-tool path (preferred — LLM tool-call) OR the direct
          endpoint path. For explicit slash, prefer direct endpoint (no LLM
          round-trip needed); for natural-language flows, prefer agent-tool.
        - branch (b) active-document-only: dispatch the EXISTING
          `SummarizeFilesDialog` wizard flow. This must use the same mechanism
          R3 uses today — do not invent a new dispatch.
        - branch (c) neither: render the interjection "Upload the file(s)
          you'd like me to summarize" as a single Assistant message in the
          chat thread. Do NOT invoke any playbook.
      Keep the helper pure (input → routing decision); the dispatch side-
      effects live alongside the existing ConversationPane dispatch wiring.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Back-Compat (Wizard Flow Unchanged)">
      Smoke test the existing `SummarizeFilesDialog` wizard flow on a
      LegalWorkspace surface (NOT via the SpaarkeAi chat shell): confirm the
      modal opens, the SSE stream completes, and the result renders. The wizard
      is consumed in places OUTSIDE the ConversationPane dispatcher (e.g.,
      LegalWorkspace, SummarizeFilesWizard solution); those consumers MUST be
      unaffected by the change. Capture the smoke-test evidence in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Add Frontend Tests">
      Add or update component tests covering: (a) the description string in
      `DEFAULT_SLASH_COMMANDS` (snapshot or direct assertion); (b) tri-mode
